ont><br>     <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> VI software migration control = farking awful!</span><hr size=1> IRL I work in the IT industry, and have done for quite a few years now.  Reasonably regularly I have to move patches of software from test into Production.  If I was as poor as Verant at moving working software from Test into Prod, and then finding I've missed bits, so now Prod is buggy, my arse would have been kicked out the door years ago.<br>
<br>
Surely someone in Verant knows how to migrate software from Test to Production???  Those of us in the 'real' software world know that you make 120% certain that you have moved everything, then you test it all before you tell Joe Public 'Yep, go for your life'.<br>
<br>
And don't get me started on needing 13 hours to patch software.  Jesus wept, are they typing in the new code by hand or something?<br>
<br>
Nem pissed off coz I was looking forward to a good night of EQ, but got a 'Sorry we fucked up last night with our big patch, so we got to patch again' message. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/unemeantrueheart.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Nemean Trueheart</A> at: 5/31/01 6:16:57 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#F5F5DC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uvydas.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Vydas</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(5/31/01 6:27:25 am)</font><br>     <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: VI software migration control = farking awful!</span><hr size=1> It's true, what you say - change control seems to be an inordinate challenge to these folks, and one they have not, over time, been able to overcome.<br>
<br>
My own strong suspicion is that their test environment is either sadly lack, or, alternatively, that significant pieces are missing, such as external interface issues (meaning they are not able to predict or test how the changes in each patch will impact network interfaces). <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ucreac.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Creac</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(5/31/01 6:45:56 am)</font><br>     <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: VI software migration control = farking awful!</span><hr size=1> Well, firstly they made some rather major changes, as I understand it.<br>
<br>
Secondly, they're pushing massive amounts of data to each server - server being a relative term since it implies singular when in fact each world is a cluster of machines.<br>
<br>
Thirdly, if you really wanna complain but also talk with someone who knows what they're talking about - visit chat late in the evenings and look for Ops-Zalshea in a red name.  She's one of the people responsible for moving data and doing the patches.  Might help you understand things a little more. <p>Creac Peregrinate - Outrider<BR><font><I>In friends we find hope</I></font><BR>Creac@prexus.com</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#F5F5DC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uvydas.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Vydas</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(5/31/01 6:52:23 am)</font><br>     <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: VI software migration control = farking awful!</span><hr size=1> Creac, though, as you probably know, most people who work in IT (and in this case, Nem specifically) routinely make major systems changes, and sometimes to very complicated systems.<br>
<br>
VI has, in my opinion, improved radically from their original testing which seemed to be unit, or one change testing, to being able to perform impact analysis and test individual changes in their overall *internal* environment.  There's a lot less of that type of error than their used to be, and hats off to them for espying and addressing the problems they had in the past.<br>
<br>
However, they continue to, on a regular basis (like almost every patch) have to perform emergency patches directly thereafter, often to deal with external issues.  That's why I made the point I did, above - they have a long way to go when it comes to networking issues before they have achieved an acceptable level of consistent performance. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ucreac.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Creac</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(5/31/01 6:56:38 am)</font><br>     <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: VI software migration control = farking awful!</span><hr size=1> Sure, Vydas - my mistake.  What would I know? <p>Creac Peregrinate - Outrider<BR><font><I>In friends we find hope</I></font><BR>Creac@prexus.com</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#F5F5DC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/utheskyfyre.showPublicProfile?language=EN>The Skyfyre</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(5/31/01 9:14:00 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: VI software migration control = farking awful!</span><hr size=1> I work as a system administrator for a rather large internet service, and I've seen lots of people make much larger mistakes than that.  However when they do, my company makes every effort to ensure that the same mistakes do not happen again.  We have millions and millions of eyeballs on our service every single day, we serve up urls per day in the billions range, and every major outage we have usually makes the news.  When you have that kind of pressure on you, you HAVE to make the stuff work right, and work right the first time.<br>
<br>
Verant doesn't have that kind of pressure.  They run a game that no one in their own company takes seriously.  I guess their customer service has improved some, but as far as actually developing and improving the game they have come up really short on the technical end.  The same problems they have always had happen repeatedly, over and over again, and it's getting a bit silly at this point.  If you have the same mistakes over and over, that's a technical problem.  If they aren't corrected, that's something that management needs to get on top of and do everything possible to ensure that their stuff gets fixed.  If management doesn't care to get involved and doesn't feel it's not important enough to fix, then I wonder how they will explain to their bosses why their client base isn't continuing to grow as expected.  Is it possibly because too many users try to get on one time, find all the servers down due to a botched patch, and merely assume the game doesn't work and return it?  Hmmm... <p><center>Khaedron Skyfyre <BR>
60th level Crusader, <BR>
Prexus<BR></center>
<img src=http://members.aol.com/deathbecomesyou/58sig.jpg></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/upetoffen.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Petoffen</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(5/31/01 10:55:46 am)</font><br>     <br>Community Supporter<br> <BR><img src=http://members.home.net/craig234/eq/petportrait.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: VI software migration control = farking awful!</span><hr size=1> Khaedron, I thought you said you were high-school age? <p>Arch Mage 60, Master of the epic elemental magics, collector of robes<BR>
<a href="http://members.home.net/craig234/"target="web"><img src="http://members.home.net/craig234/eq/sig/petquotecrakerrcaniseepetattack.gif" border="0"></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/upetoffen.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Petoffen</A> at: 5/31/01 10:56:10 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#F5F5DC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/utheskyfyre.showPublicProfile?language=EN>The Skyfyre</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(5/31/01 5:26:46 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: VI software migration control = farking awful!</span><hr size=1> Mmmm, nope, I'm 23 pet.  I've been working with my particular company since high school age though :).  Been with them about 4 years now. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uglomfyrestormm.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Glom Fyrestormm</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_fire.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(6/5/01 12:59:52 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: VI software migration control = farking awful!</span><hr size=1> Actually, I think VI is probably more of a slave to a flawed architecture, or an architecture which is being bent in a way which was not originally forseen.<br>
<br>
They were probably pushed to get a product out the door sometime two years ago, and like many companies, probably sacrificed quality for dev time in order to ship.  Sadly, many experienced software engineers can tell you horror stories of maintaining products which were forced out the door in this manner.<br>
